      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Automotive suppliers, parts manufacturers, and aftermarket dealers across Malaysia face a critical challenge: protecting expensive, precision-engineered components during shipping without adding excessive weight or cost. Honeycomb cardboard panels offer the ideal solution — engineered strength at a fraction of traditional foam packaging weight and cost.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Why Honeycomb Cardboard for Automotive Shipping</h2>
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Superior Impact Protection</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Honeycomb's unique cellular structure absorbs impacts that would damage traditional cardboard. Engine blocks, transmissions, and assemblies stay pristine during rough handling, loading/unloading, and transport across Peninsular Malaysia.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Significant Weight Reduction</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Honeycomb weighs 50% less than foam padding. Lighter shipments = lower shipping costs. A transmission wrapped in honeycomb vs. foam can save RM 50–150 in freight per unit — substantial for high-volume suppliers.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Cost-Effective vs. Foam & Plastic</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Honeycomb cardboard costs 40–50% less than closed-cell foam or plastic bubble packaging, while providing better protection. ROI is immediate, especially for bulk shipments.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Fully Customizable</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Cut honeycomb panels to exact dimensions. Create corner protectors, curved wraps, and custom cushioning layouts for any automotive component — no design is too complex.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Environmentally Responsible</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Honeycomb is 100% recyclable cardboard. Modern automotive buyers value sustainability — suppliers using eco-friendly packaging gain competitive advantage and customer loyalty.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Packaging Automotive Components with Honeycomb</h2>
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Engine Blocks & Cylinder Heads</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Wrap entire engine in 2–3 layers of honeycomb cardboard. Use corner protectors at all edges. Secure with industrial tape. Place in sturdy carton with additional honeycomb buffer at bottom and sides. Result: zero damage during international or domestic shipping.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Transmissions & Assemblies</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Complex assemblies require custom wrapping. Honeycomb adapts to irregular shapes. Wrap tightly, tape securely, cushion protruding elements. Use honeycomb sheets as additional shock absorbers within cartons.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Brake Systems & Suspension Parts</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Brake assemblies and suspension components have precision surfaces sensitive to scratches. Honeycomb + tissue paper wrap prevents cosmetic damage. Critical for OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) quality standards.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Electronics & Control Modules</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Lightweight but sensitive. Honeycomb with anti-static considerations works well. Creates protective micro-environment within carton while minimizing package weight for fast, economical shipping.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Bulk Part Shipments (Fasteners, Brackets)</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Use honeycomb sheets as dividers within cartons to organize mixed parts. Prevents shifting, reduces damage, and makes inventory management easier at the receiving end.</p>
      </section>

